The ease with which Tac. might have avoided the slightly mixed metaphor‚ by transposing ‘instructus' and ‘armatus,' renders it highly probable that the MSS. have preserved the original reading. The author’s reason for writing, as he did, seems to have been his dislike of the figura etymologica. Cf. note c. 2217. For an analogous inconcinnity, see Cio. de orat. II 21, 88 cited by Binde p. 46.

For the entire paragraph from deinde-exierit, Cicero was again laid under contribution. Cf. esp. de orat.
